description.raw:
This document describes the overall architecture and development process for a Gazebo plugin  which works as a server for the RoboCup 3D Soccer Simulation League.

There is a partial implementation [here](https://github.com/osrf/robocup_3d_simulation) which uses ROS, but @caguero and I thought of making a new implementation based purely on Gazebo to decrease complexity. A great part of what's already been done can be ported to a plugin.

#!/osrf/gazebo_design/src/05b163827042b70ecc8c29a1fe7fbfe05cda17df/robocup3ds/robocup3ds.md?at=robocup3ds

